Seems like the plea of most South Africans complaining about data prices have been heard. Earlier this month Vodacom announced that it will be reducing data prices by 30% from the first of April. MTN is also expected to announce solutions to reduce data costs today. • Editor’s note: This livestream has ended. Watch the recording above. JOHANNESBURG - MTN is set to make an announcement on data prices on Friday. MTN SA CEO Godfrey Motsa will be joined by Minister of the Department of Communications and Digital Technologies, Stella Ndabeni-Abrahams. READ: Vodacom data prices will fall This comes after the Competition Commission announced that network giant Vodacom will reduce monthly data prices by at least 30 percent. This will be effective from 1 April.